# Implementation Plan - HR Module & Persistence Fixes

This plan aims to fix the current backend build errors, complete the HR module integration with Senior HCM, and refine the frontend to ensure it's ready for public access.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The `/api/hr/recruitment-insights` endpoint in [Program.cs](file:///c:/Users/RPA_COMERCIAL/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/login_system/backend/Program.cs) is currently broken (missing its route mapping line), which prevents the backend from building. I will fix this.

## Proposed Changes

### Backend (C# / .NET)

#### [MODIFY] [Program.cs](file:///c:/Users/RPA_COMERCIAL/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/login_system/backend/Program.cs)
- Fix the `/api/hr/recruitment-insights` endpoint by adding the missing `app.MapGet` mapping.
- Implement `/api/hr/vacancies/{id}/candidates` to fetch real candidates from the Senior API (or refine the mock if the API is restricted).
- Ensure all paths for static files are robust for different execution environments.

---

### Frontend (HTML/JS)

#### [MODIFY] [rh.html](file:///c:/Users/RPA_COMERCIAL/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/login_system/frontend/rh.html)
- Change `API_BASE` from a hardcoded Ngrok URL to a relative path or use `window.location.origin` to avoid 404s when the tunnel changes.
- Connect the [viewCandidates](file:///c:/Users/RPA_COMERCIAL/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/login_system/frontend/rh.html#363-392) function to the new backend endpoint.
- Improve the Insights UI to handle loading states better.

---

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Run `dotnet build` to ensure the backend compiles correctly.
- Test the `/api/hr/vacancies` and `/api/hr/recruitment-insights` endpoints using `curl` or a temporary test script.

### Manual Verification
1. Open the application via the browser.
2. Navigate to the "Recursos Humanos" -> "Vagas em Aberto" page.
3. Verify that the vacancies are listed and the insights dashboard displays data.
4. Click on "Ver Candidatos" for a vacancy and verify that the drawer opens and shows candidate information.
